In [804]:
#start hyper parameter tuning, to find optimum max depth in rnage of 1, 50
training_list = []
testing_list = []
for max_d in range(1,50):
  model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=max_d, random_state=100)
  model.fit(X_train,y_train)
  training_list.append(model.score(X_train,y_train))
  testing_list.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
  print('The Training Accuracy for max_depth {} is:'.format(max_d), model.score(X_train, y_train))
  print('The Validation Accuracy for max_depth {} is:'.format(max_d), model.score(X_test, y_test))
  #print('')
In [805]:
depth = pd.DataFrame(training_list, columns = ['Training Accuracy'])
depth.index = depth.index + 1
depth.insert(1, 'Testing Accuracy', testing_list)
depth.loc[depth['Testing Accuracy'] == depth['Testing Accuracy'].max()]

#start hyper parameter tuning, to find optimum  leaf nodes
leaves_training = []
leaves_testing = []
for leaves in range(2, 300):
  model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_leaf_nodes=leaves, random_state=100)
  model.fit(X_train,y_train)
  leaves_training.append(model.score(X_train,y_train))
  leaves_testing.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
